In our analysis, we employed a funnel plot to evaluate the long-term efficacy between the two treatment groups, specifically examining OS at 1-year and 2-year follow-ups, as well as PFS at the same time points. The results of each funnel plot demonstrated that the respective data points from the included studies were all encompassed within the funnel plot and displayed a generally symmetrical distribution (
Figure 4
). In general, the likelihood of publication bias is minimal, given the symmetrical distribution of scatter points within the inverted funnel plot.
